===message:I'm a little bit torn on this one.  I do not really think that Evans was crazy or used "low-mentality".  Like I posted previously.  He used his words in a way that convinced a great deal of followers. If you think about some of the aspects in his speech, it can be closely compared to our pledge.  One nation, Under God, Indivisible..... I think these were the points he was trying to discuss.  He did not believe that certain groups could remain "Indivisible" or Uphold all American ideals because they had their own heritage/culture/background.  Once again, I'm not stating that his views are correct. I'm just stating that I do indeed think that he was an educated man who felt very strong for American ideals.
